It was brand new, in the white, and unfired when purchased. Parkerization job was done by Schuff's Parkerizing. The barrel is timed and torqued properly.Rifle does have scuffs near barrel shank from slipping in the barrel vice. This is covered by the handguards and there is no rust to speak of anywhere on the rifle. Included picture wihtout handguards shows scuffing.The gun is 922r compliant when using US made magazines. I wanted to keep as many internals as possible original.Must be 18yrs or older. Must present valid KY state ID. Must sign a bill of sale. Higher resolution photos available upon request.

THE LEFT SIDE OF THE RIFLE RECEIVER IS A LITTLE BETTER WITH THE BLUE LOSS AROUND THE EJECTION PORT AND DOWN BY THE LEVER WHERE YOU CARRY THIS RIFLE. THIS IS A FLAT BAND WINCHESTER WHICH IS VERY RARE.
